# Plugin compiled shim binaries — published via GitHub Releases, downloaded
# lazily by the launcher (bin/prixmaviz-mcp + bin/prixmaviz-mcp.cmd, both
# tracked). Allow-list pattern: ignore everything in bin/ that looks like a
# compiled binary, but keep the launcher scripts.
src-tauri/resources/plugin/bin/prixmaviz-mcp-*
src-tauri/resources/plugin/bin/*.exe.partial
src-tauri/resources/plugin/bin/*.partial

# Runtime test project roots
.prixmaviz-test/

# Runtime workspace state (Cycle 3 era, also covers ad-hoc local testing)
.prixmaviz/

# HyperFrames-installed agent skills (third-party content, install via
# `npx skills add heygen-com/hyperframes`). Symlinked under .claude/skills/
# for CC discovery.
.agents/
.claude/skills/
skills-lock.json

# HyperFrames render outputs (large MP4s, re-renderable from sources;
# committed renders live as GitHub Release assets instead).
docs/marketing/hero-demo/renders/
# HyperFrames lint/inspect thumbnails (regenerated on every `npm run check`)
docs/marketing/hero-demo/.thumbnails/
